    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00119_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note resp="#rmb" type="editorial" place="top"><hi rend="underline">From Bethuel's
                    Mother</hi></note>
            <opener>
                <name type="place">Queensbury,</name>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1875-03-14">March, the 14h 75</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend</salute>
            </opener>

            <p><choice>
                    <sic>ireceived</sic>
                    <corr>I received</corr>
                </choice> your kind letter some time ago <choice>
                    <sic>iwas</sic>
                    <corr>I was</corr>
                </choice> truly glad to hear from you <choice>
                    <sic>iwas</sic>
                    <corr>I was</corr>
                </choice> sick and am not well now <choice>
                    <sic>itook</sic>
                    <corr>I took</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>aheavy</sic>
                    <corr>a heavy</corr>
                </choice> cold had the Doctor Called once <choice>
                    <sic>ihave</sic>
                    <corr>I have</corr>
                </choice> some Cough yet but go around the house and sit up the most of the time <choice>
                    <sic>an</sic>
                    <corr>and</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>inhopes</sic>
                    <corr>in hopes</corr>
                </choice> of going out in <choice>
                    <sic>afew</sic>
                    <corr>a few</corr>
                </choice> days we got <choice>
                    <sic>Bethuels</sic>
                    <corr>Bethuel's</corr>
                </choice><ptr target="loc.01930_n3"/> papers and your picture and sent all the
                things <choice>
                    <sic>overto</sic>
                    <corr>over to</corr>
                </choice> him we all see the picture and was very much pleased to see it Mary said
                that is the man that saved our brother's life to one of our neighbours Mary and
                David<ptr target="loc.01930_n5"/> has gone to <pb xml:id="leaf001v"
                    facs="loc_jc.00120_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <note resp="#rmb" type="editorial" place="top">Mrs Smith (Bethuel's Mother)</note>
                her brother, Halsey Smiths<ptr target="loc.01932_n2"/>
                <choice>
                    <sic>avisiting</sic>
                    <corr>a visiting</corr>
                </choice> now they will go to their boat the last of the month he says he will try
                and find you when he goes to <choice>
                    <sic>philidelphia</sic>
                    <corr><name>Philadelphia</name></corr>
                </choice> perhaps you will see them both this summer <choice>
                    <sic>Bethuels</sic>
                    <corr>Bethuel's</corr>
                </choice> youngest little boy has <choice>
                    <sic>ben</sic>
                    <corr>been</corr>
                </choice> scalded with tea on his stomach they sent for the Doctor that is the last
                we have heard that is <choice>
                    <sic>akind</sic>
                    <corr>a kind</corr>
                </choice> hearted little boy and <choice>
                    <sic>agood</sic>
                    <corr>a good</corr>
                </choice> child <choice>
                    <sic>ilove</sic>
                    <corr>I love</corr>
                </choice> him you mail your letters right we live in the south west part of the town
                if you should mail your letter Queensbury it would go to the north part <choice>
                    <sic>avillage</sic>
                    <corr>a village</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>bythe</sic>
                    <corr>by the</corr>
                </choice> name of the rider we <choice>
                    <sic>dont</sic>
                    <corr>don't</corr>
                </choice> go there once <choice>
                    <sic>ayear</sic>
                    <corr>a year</corr>
                </choice>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_jc.00121_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                <choice>
                    <sic>i</sic>
                    <corr>I</corr>
                </choice> thank you for all your <choice>
                    <sic>preasants</sic>
                    <corr>presents</corr>
                </choice> you sent me <choice>
                    <sic>i</sic>
                    <corr>I</corr>
                </choice> read with <choice>
                    <sic>intrest</sic>
                    <corr>interest</corr>
                </choice> and thought of our kind friend although far away perhaps we all may see <choice>
                    <sic>eachother</sic>
                    <corr>each other</corr>
                </choice> yet our Children are anxious to see you the picture you sent Bethuel looks
                some like my grandfather Deen<ptr target="n5001"/> that is my <choice>
                    <sic>fathers</sic>
                    <corr>father's</corr>
                </choice> father if Harvy Allen and Sally<ptr target="loc.01932_n3"/> should go to <choice>
                    <sic>philadelphia</sic>
                    <corr>Philadelphia</corr>
                </choice> they will find you <choice>
                    <sic>ishould</sic>
                    <corr>I should</corr>
                </choice> like to have your picture Bethuel has got the one you sent to his father
                and me <choice>
                    <sic>iwas</sic>
                    <corr>I was</corr>
                </choice> to Halsey Smith when <choice>
                    <sic>irote</sic>
                    <corr>I wrote</corr>
                </choice> the other letter to you <choice>
                    <sic>istayed</sic>
                    <corr>I stayed</corr>
                </choice> there <choice>
                    <sic>sevral</sic>
                    <corr>several</corr>
                </choice> days they live about two miles from <choice>
                    <sic>glensfalls</sic>
                    <corr><name>Glens Falls</name></corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>iwent</sic>
                    <corr>I went</corr>
                </choice> to meeting one Sunday evening and enjoyed my <choice>
                    <sic>meting</sic>
                    <corr>meeting</corr>
                </choice> firstrate <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_jc.00122_large.jpg" type="verso"
                /> there was 1 baptised and <choice>
                    <sic>sevral</sic>
                    <corr>several</corr>
                </choice> more received in <choice>
                    <sic>ful</sic>
                    <corr>full</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>felowship</sic>
                    <corr>fellowship</corr>
                </choice> with the Church there has <choice>
                    <sic>ben</sic>
                    <corr>been</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>areformation</sic>
                    <corr>a reformation</corr>
                </choice> to <choice>
                    <sic>glens falls</sic>
                    <corr>Glens Falls</corr>
                </choice> this winter <choice>
                    <sic>irejoiced</sic>
                    <corr>I rejoiced</corr>
                </choice> to see it the evening <choice>
                    <sic>iwas</sic>
                    <corr>I was</corr>
                </choice> there they sung old fashioned hymns and old tunes it seemed like old times
                when <choice>
                    <sic>iwas</sic>
                    <corr>I was</corr>
                </choice> young <choice>
                    <sic>idont</sic>
                    <corr>I dont</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>now</sic>
                    <corr>know</corr>
                </choice> as you can read my <choice>
                    <sic>riting</sic>
                    <corr>writing</corr>
                </choice> but we feel anxious to hear from you and how you get along</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>god bless you with my best respects and love to you</salute>
                <signed>from Maria Smith</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>to Mr Walt Whitman</addrLine>
                </address>
                <salute>yours truly</salute>
            </closer> 
        </body> 
